EX-CONVICT Kenny Motsamai who was the leader of the Azanian People's Liberation Army (Apla) is going to Parliament. Apla was one of the once feared and most violent liberation movement army in South Africa. Motsamai was sworn in as a member of the National Council of Provinces (NCOP), by Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng. He was sentenced for killing a white traffic officer in Rustenburg in 1989 and served nearly 28 years behind bars for the murder.  